							WHAT IS A DOCKER IMAGE?

 A docker image is a read-only template that contains a set of instructions for creating a container that can run on the docker platform. it provides a convenient way to package up applications and preconfigured server environments, which you can use for your own [private use for or share publicly with other docker users. each docker image contain changes to the update to docker images like form image layers. 


